channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: 'Dancing with the Stars' pro Artem Chigvintsev arrested for domestic violence
item.description: "Dancing with the Stars" pro Artem Chigvintsev has been arrested for domestic violence, according to Napa County jail records.

item.title: Shakedown or 'cheap spy novel': What did L.A. investigators do for a Chinese millionaire?
Inmate who escaped Kansas prison in dog crate dies at age 45
item.description: The escape story was featured on "Dateline" and is the inspiration behind the Lifetime movie, "Jailbreak Lovers."

item.title: 1 police officer shot and killed, 2 others wounded in Dallas shooting
item.description: One police officer has been shot and killed and two others wounded after a shooting in Dallas, Texas, authorities have confirmed.

item.title: She's a Norwegian princess. He's an American self-professed shaman. Their wedding is this weekend
Japan tosses plan to woo women with cash
item.description: A widely ridiculed Japanese government idea to woo Tokyo women into marrying men in rural areas by offering cash payouts and train tickets to matchmaking events has been scrapped, officials say.

item.title: Two-thirds of Americans say Trump unprepared to accept the election outcome: POLL
item.description: Most Americans say they and Vice President Kamala Harris alike are prepared to accept the election outcome as legitimate, a new ABC News/Ispos poll found.

item.title: Ancient humans built a bridge inside a cave on Mallorca nearly 6,000 years ago
Hiker found dead in Grand Canyon near rugged, remote Colorado River trail
item.description: A solo backpacker has been found dead near a rugged and remote trail along the Colorado River in Grand Canyon National Park, authorities in Arizona say.

item.title: 'Next question, please,' Harris brushes off question about Trump's race comments
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris talked about her changing positions in the first clips released ahead of her first televised interview since becoming the Democratic nominee.

item.title: A toddler cried non-stop during a flight. Two strangers locked her in the bathroom
Military attacked, roads blocked in Mexican cartel stronghold
item.description: There have been fears that wider violence might break out following recent detentions of top Sinaloa cartel leaders in the U.S.

item.title: WATCH: Northern lights shine as lava spews from erupting volcano in Iceland
item.description: Natural phenomena collide as an erupting volcano and the northern lights join forces to illuminate the night sky over Iceland's Reykjanes Peninsula.
